== Arnold Strongman Classic-Europe == {{Infobox sport tournament |year = 2012 |name = Arnold Strongman Classic-Europe |image = Arnclassic.jpg |caption = The official logo of the Arnold Sports Festival |location = varies, 2012 contest held in [[Madrid, Spain]] |establishment = 2012 |format = Multi-event competition |purse = $10,000 |month_played = October |current_champion = {{flagicon|LTU}} [[Zydrunas Savickas]]<ref name=autogenerated5>[http://www.ironmind.com/ironmind/opencms/Articles/2012/Oct/Zydrunas_Savickas-Wins_the_SCL_Spain-Arnold-Europe.html Zydrunas Savickas Wins SCL Spain/Arnold-Europe<!-- Bot generated title -->]</ref> }}
In 2012, the inaugural ''"Arnold Strongman Classic-Europe"'' contest was formed, and is a joint promotion between Arnold Schwarzenegger, Jim Lorimer (Arnold Sports Festival co-promoter), Dr. Rafael Santonja (president of the International Federation of Body Building, "IFBB") as well as [[Strength athletics in the United States|American Strongman Corporation]] and [[Strongman Champions League]].<ref name=autogenerated3>[http://www.ironmind.com/ironmind/opencms/Articles/2012/Sep/Strongman_Champions_League_Coming_to_the_Arnold_Classic-Europe.html Strongman Champions League Coming to the Arnold Classic–Europe<!-- Bot generated title -->]</ref>
The ''"Arnold Strongman Classic-Europe"'' contest will differ significantly from the format of the original Arnold Strongman Classic event, with less of an emphasis on brute strength and heavy events, and will include a wider variety of events and some speed/loading events similar to [[Strongman Champions League]] and [[World's Strongest Man]] contests.<ref name=autogenerated3 /> The format change is due largely in part to the event being broadcast and televised in 85 countries.<ref name=autogenerated3 />
=== 2012: Arnold Strongman Classic-Europe === The 2012 contest was held in [[Madrid, Spain]] on Oct. 13 & 14, 2012, the event was sponsored by [[Maximum Human Performance|MHP]].<ref name=autogenerated3 /> The contest is included as part of the 2012 [[Strongman Champions League]] season, and competitors earned points towards the annual SCL overall title.<ref name=autogenerated3 /> The inaugural contest was won by 6 time Arnold Strongman champion and reigning [[World's Strongest Man]] [[Zydrunas Savickas]] of [[Lithuania]], who was also the 2012 SCL overall champion.<ref name=autogenerated5 />
'''Dates:''' October 13–14, 2012<ref name=autogenerated5 /> '''[[Madrid]], [[Spain]]''' {| class="wikitable" !Position !Name !Country !Points !Prize |- | 1. || [[Zydrunas Savickas]] || {{flag|LTU}} || 47 || $10,000<ref name=autogenerated5 /> |- | 2. || [[Krzysztof Radzikowski]] || {{flag|POL}} || 44 || |- | 3. || [[Vytautas Lalas]] || {{flag|LTU}} || 42.5 || |- | 4. || [[Mike Burke (strongman)|Mike Burke]] || {{flag|USA}} || 37.5 || |- | 5. || [[Mikhail Koklyaev]] || {{flag|RUS}} || 37 || |- | 6. || [[Hafþór Júlíus Björnsson]] || {{flag|ISL}} || 36.5 || |- | 7. || [[Mike Jenkins (strongman)|Mike Jenkins]] || {{flag|USA}} || 35 || |- | 8. || [[Ervin Katona]] || {{flag|Serbia}} || 22 || |- | 9. || [[Konstiantyn Ilin]] || {{flag|UKR}} || 16 || |- |10. || [[Lauri Nami]] || {{flag|EST}} || 14 || |- |}
== Arnold Strongman Classic Australia == {{Infobox sport tournament |year = 2015 |name = Arnold Strongman Classic Australia |image = Arnclassic.jpg |caption = The official logo of the Arnold Sports Festival |location = varies, 2015 contest held in [[Melbourne Convention and Exhibition Centre]] |establishment = 2015 |format = Multi-event competition |purse = $10,000 |month_played = October |current_champion = }}
In 2015, the inaugural ''"Arnold Strongman Classic Australia"'' contest was formed, and is a joint promotion between Arnold Schwarzenegger, Jim Lorimer (Arnold Sports Festival co-promoter), Dr. Rafael Santonja (president of the [[International Federation of BodyBuilding & Fitness]], "IFBB") as well as [[Strength athletics in the Australia|Australian Strongman Corporation]] and [[Strongman Champions League]].<ref>http://arnoldstrongman.com.au/</ref><ref>http://arnoldclassic.com.au/</ref>
== Arnold Amateur Strongman World Championships == In 2010, the Arnold Amateur contest was formed by Dione Wessels.<ref name=autogenerated4>[http://www.ironmind.com/ironmind/opencms/Articles/2010/Mar/Mike_Jenkins_Wins_Amateur_Strongman_Title_at_the_Arnold.html Mike Jenkins Wins Amateur Strongman Title at the Arnold<!-- Bot generated title -->]</ref> The contest is open to amateur strongman competitors from all over the world. The winner of the contest receives their pro card, and an invite to the next year's Arnold Strongman Classic event.<ref name=autogenerated4 /> [[Mike Jenkins (strongman)|Mike Jenkins]] won the inaugural contest in 2010,<ref name=autogenerated4 />[[Mateusz Baron]] from [[Poland]] was the 2011 winner,<ref name=autogenerated6>[http://www.ironmind.com/ironmind/opencms/Articles/2011/Mar/Matesz_Baron_Wins_ASC_Arnold_Amateur_Strongman_World_Championships.html Matesz Baron Wins ASC Arnold Amateur Strongman World Championships<!-- Bot generated title -->]</ref> and [[Adam Scherr]] was the 2012 winner.<ref name=autogenerated1>[http://www.ironmind.com/ironmind/opencms/Articles/2012/Mar/Adam_Scherr_Wins_Arnold_ASC_Amateur_Strongman_World_Championships.html Adam Scherr Wins Arnold ASC Amateur Strongman World Championships<!-- Bot generated title -->]</ref>
