{{Unreferenced|date=August 2008}} {{Infobox baseball team| Name =Cienfuegos| Logo =[[Image:CFG logo.png|150px]]| Founded =[[1977-78 Cuban National Series|1977-78]]| Nickname =''Elefantes'' ([[Elephant]]s)| League =[[Cuban National Series]]| Division =Group B| Location =[[Cienfuegos]]| Stadium =[[Cinco de Septiembre Stadium]], [[Cienfuegos]]| Season =[[2005-06 Cuban National Series|2005-06]]| Record =35-54 (4th, Group B)| Playoffs =Did not qualify for playoffs| Manager =[[Narciso Ferrer]]| h_cap =008822| h_pattern_cap=| h_leftarm=008822| h_pattern_la=| h_body=008822| h_pattern_b=_baseball| h_rightarm=008822| h_pattern_ra=| h_pants=000000| h_pattern_pants=| h_socks=000000|}}
'''Cienfuegos''' is a [[baseball]] team in the [[Cuban National Series]]. Based in the southern city of [[Cienfuegos]], the ''Camaroneros'' had their best season in their second year of existence, finishing fourth in the National Series. They have never come close to replicating that success.
The ''Camaroneros'' had two pitchers on [[Cuba national baseball team|Cuba's team]] at the [[2006 World Baseball Classic]]: [[Adiel Palma]] and [[Yosvany Pérez]].
==Current roster== *'''Catchers''': Osvaldo Arias, Adir Ferrán, Camilche Veloz, Edelkis Reyes *'''Infielders''': Pedro José Rodríguez, José M. Pérez, Yusel Valdés, Jesús Reyes, Jorge Rodríguez, Asniel Marín, Andy Sarduy, Adriano García *'''Outfielders''': José Dariel Abréu, Yosvani Lazo, Alexander Martínez, Yoelvis Leyva, Yusniel Ibáñez, Lázaro Rodríguez *'''Pitchers''': Alexander Quintero, [[Norberto González]], Duniel Ibarra, Leovet Cardoso, [[Adiel Palma]], Yasniel Hidalgo, Yasmany Fernández, Samuel Ruiz, [[Yosvany Pérez]], Randy Gutiérrez, Reiniel Cantero e Islet Santiago
==National Series MVPs== *1980 [[Pedro José Rodríguez]] *2011 [[José Dariel Abreu]]
