{{Use dmy dates|date=June 2013}} :''This article is about the [[New York Mets]]' Cow-Bell Man. For the [[New York Yankees]]' Cow-Bell Man, a title jointly held by Ali Ramirez and Milton Ousland, see [[Bleacher Creatures#The Cow-Bell Man|Bleacher Creatures]].'' [[File:Cowbell Man on April 13, 2009 (cropped).jpg|thumb|left|Cowbell Man in 2009]] [[Image:Cowbellman.jpg|200px|thumb|right|Cowbell Man]] [[Image:Cowbellman-091815.jpg|200px|thumb|right|Cowbell Man in 2015]] '''Edwin "Eddie" Boison''', known as '''Cow-Bell Man''', is a stadium fixture for the [[New York Mets]].<ref name="Davis">{{cite web|url=http://www.queenscourier.com/articles/2008/04/09/news/local/news34.txt|title=Memories, history fill Shea|last=Davis|first=Pete|date=9 April 2008|work=The Queens Courier|accessdate=18 June 2010|deadurl=yes|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110716022445/http://www.queenscourier.com/articles/2008/04/09/news/local/news34.txt|archivedate=16 July 2011|df=dmy-all}}</ref> He can be seen at nearly every home game at [[Citi Field]], wandering around the concourses while banging a [[Cowbell (instrument)|cowbell]]. He typically wears personalized jerseys with the sobriquet Cowbellman. In 2009, he wore a batting practice jersey with the number 15, which from 2005-2011 was assigned to outfielder [[Carlos Beltrán]].<ref>{{cite web|author= |url=http://bleacherreport.com/articles/385789-the-story-of-cow-bell-man |title=The Story of New York Mets Fan: Cow-Bell Man |publisher=Bleacherreport.com |date= |accessdate=2015-06-12}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://newyork.cbslocal.com/2011/07/28/colemans-corner-what-is-carlos-beltrans-mets-legacy/ |title=Ed Coleman: What Is Carlos Beltran’s New York Mets Legacy? Slugger A Soon-To-Be San Francisco Giant « CBS New York |publisher=Newyork.cbslocal.com |date=2011-07-28 |accessdate=2015-06-12}}</ref> Prior to the Mets' acquisition of Beltran, Cow-Bell Man's jersey featured the number 10, worn by Endy Chavez. Cow-Bell Man is usually seen strolling around Citi-Field interacting with the fans. As of September 2015, Cow-Bell Man wears a Met jersey with "Cow-Bell Man" and #21. Now wears 52 like Cespedes.
