{{Infobox cricket ground | ground_name = Ditchmore Lane | nickname = | country = England | image = | location = [[Stevenage]], [[Hertfordshire]] | establishment = 1921 (first recorded match) | seating_capacity = | end1 = | end2 = | year1 = 1921&ndash;2000 | club1 = [[Hertfordshire County Cricket Club|Hertfordshire]] | date = 25 July | year = 2010 | source = https://cricketarchive.com/Archive/Grounds/11/756.html Ground profile }}
'''Ditchmore Lane''' is a [[cricket]] ground in [[Stevenage]], [[Hertfordshire]]. The first recorded match on the ground was in 1921, when [[Hertfordshire County Cricket Club|Hertfordshire]] played their first [[Minor Counties Championship]] match which was against [[Buckinghamshire County Cricket Club|Buckinghamshire]]. From 1921 to 2000, the ground played host to 41 Minor Counties Championship matches <ref>[https://cricketarchive.com/Archive/Grounds/11/756_minc.html Minor Counties Championship Matches played on Ditchmore Lane]</ref> and 2 [[MCCA Knockout Trophy]] matches.<ref>[https://cricketarchive.com/Archive/Grounds/11/756_mint.html Minor Counties Trophy Matches played on Ditchmore Lane]</ref>
The ground hosted a single [[List-A cricket|List-A]] match in the [[1969 Gillette Cup]] between Hertfordshire and [[Devon County Cricket Club|Devon]].<ref>[https://cricketarchive.com/Archive/Grounds/11/756_a.html List-A Matches played on Ditchmore Lane]</ref>
In local domestic cricket, Digswell Park is the home ground of [[Stevenage Cricket Club]]<ref>[http://stevenage.hitscricket.com/default.aspx Steveange Cricket Club]</ref> who play in the Home Counties Premier Cricket League Division Two. The cricket club has existed since 1878 and is the oldest sports club in Stevenage.
