{{Infobox baseball biography |name=Kim Jeong-hu |image_size= |team= |number= |position=[[Pitcher]] |birth_date={{Birth date and age|1988|09|26|df=y}} |bats=Right |throws=Right |debutleague=[[Korea Baseball Championship|KBO]] |debutyear=2013 |debutteam=SK Wyverns |finaldate= |finalyear= |finalteam= |statleague=KBO |teams= *[[Sangmu Phoenix (baseball)|Sangmu Phoenix]] ({{by|2011}}–{{by|2012}}) (army) *[[SK Wyverns]] ({{by|2013}}) *[[Doosan Bears]] ({{by|2018}}) |highlights= |update=|birth_place=[[Seoul]]}}
'''Kim Jeong-hu''' ({{korean|김정후}}; born 26 September 1988) is a South Korean professional baseball pitcher who is currently a free agent. He graduated from [[Dankook University]] and was selected by the [[SK Wyverns]] in the second draft in 2013. Kim joined the SK Wyverns, but after injury and personal reasons he came out of the team after the 2014 season. He turned to pitcher and worked in Japan's independent league. He returned to South Korea in 2018 and joined the [[Doosan Bears]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.koreabaseball.com/Record/Player/PitcherDetail/Basic.aspx?playerId=61962|title=KBO 홈페이지 player info|last=스포츠투아이|first=|date=|website=|language=ko|archive-url=|archive-date=|dead-url=|access-date=23 April 2018}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=http://sports.donga.com/3/all/20180418/89680226/3|title=[베이스볼 피플] ‘외야수 김경근’은 어떻게 ‘파이어볼러 김정후’로 다시 태어났나|work=sports.donga.com|access-date=2018-04-23|language=ko}}</ref>
