The '''New Zealand Coaches Hall of Fame''' is sponsored by [[Athletics New Zealand]] and the Athletics Coaches Association of New Zealand. Founded in 2006, the purpose of the [[Hall of Fame]] is to "increase the recognition and status of [[coach (sport)|coaches]]." It is the first coaching Hall of Fame established in [[Australasia]].<ref>http://www.athletics.org.nz/Article.aspx?ID=1464 Retrieved 2009-03-08.</ref><ref>http://wikirun.com/New_Zealand_Coaches_Hall_of_Fame Retrieved 2009-03-08.</ref>
The coaches inducted into the Hall of Fame are: *[[Jim Bellwood]] *[[Arthur Eustace]] *[[Arch Jelley]]<ref>{{cite news |last1=Burgess |first1=Michael |title=Big read: The oldest Olympic coach in the world? |url=http://www.nzherald.co.nz/olympics/news/article.cfm?c_id=502&objectid=11667747 |accessdate=3 July 2016 |work=[[The New Zealand Herald]] |date=3 July 2016}}</ref> *[[Arthur Lydiard]]
