'''Samba Adama''' (born 12 November 1955) is a [[Mauritania]]n [[freestyle wrestler|freestyle]] and [[Greco-Roman wrestler]]

Adama competed for [[Mauritania]] at the [[1988 Summer Olympics]] in both disciplines of wrestling, but lost both group matches in each discipline by falls so didn't advance to the next round in either.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.sports-reference.com/olympics/athletes/ad/samba-adama-1.html|title=Samba Adama Bio, Stats, and Results|website=Olympics at Sports-Reference.com|language=en|access-date=2018-05-14}}</ref>

